{#- LLM-facing text is English-only: Cyrillic uses roughly 2–3x more tokens per word.
    This Jinja comment is stripped and never sent to the model.
    Single-pass LightRAG query (no separate plan LLM): user intent first, then seed
    subtasks / hints, then recent thread context (newest first). The whole render is
    token-capped from the END (trim_from_end_tokens), so the physical tail = oldest
    thread context is dropped first, never the user intent or subtasks.
    Variables: incoming_user_message (str); subtasks (list[str], seed only);
    extra_instructions (str | None); thread_context (str | None, newest-first). -#}
{{ incoming_user_message }}
{%- if subtasks %}

--- planned subtasks (retrieve context for each) ---
{%- for st in subtasks %}
- {{ st }}
{%- endfor %}
{%- endif %}
{%- if extra_instructions %}

--- additional retrieval hints ---
{{ extra_instructions }}
{%- endif %}
{%- if thread_context %}

--- recent thread context (newest first) ---
{{ thread_context }}
{%- endif %}
